cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing an infrastructure for health monitoring applications that involves networking equipment. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes a fog computing infrastructure that involves distributed processing and backup servers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper uses a Mixed Integer Linear Programming (MILP) model to optimize the infrastructure. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper involves optimization of energy consumption. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper involves processing and analysis of Electrocardiogram (ECG) signals.
